summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on the UN operation in Cyprus, 
particularly the call to address the humanitarian issue of missing persons urgently,
Noting the Government of Cyprus's agreement to extend the UN Peacekeeping Force in Cyprus (UNFICYP) due to prevailing conditions,

 Reaffirms its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;

Decides to extend UNFICYP's mandate until 15 June 2002;

Requests the Secretary-General to report on the implementation by 1 June 2002;

Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to rescind restrictions on UNFICYP's operations and restore the military status quo at Strovilia;

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
